# Secrets.
# Phase 5 introduced real ones: the DB password, the cookie secret, and the OAuth
# client secrets all live in .env. So ignore EVERY .env variant by default and
# allow back only the examples, which contain no values. Listing individual
# filenames is how a `.env.production` ends up in a public repo.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
